text: Michelle Sawyers (born 25 October 1960) is a former defender from Australia who made 13 appearances for the Australia women's national soccer team. == Playing career == Sawyers started playing in 1973 at age 13 for Coalstars SC. She would stay at Coalstars for her entire senior career, which lasted until 1992. Sawyers was later selected in the FFA International Team of the Decade for 1979–89. ==References== Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football defenders Category:Australian women's soccer players Category:Australia women's international soccer players
